radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 9 mm with enhancing wall. The appendix is fluid-filled with adjacent fat stranding. The lung bases are clear bilaterally. The liver is normal in size and attenuation. No focal hepatic lesions are identified. The spleen is normal in size and enhancement. The pancreas shows normal enhancement. The adrenal glands are unremarkable bilaterally. The kidneys display symmetric nephrograms with no evidence of hydronephrosis or mass lesion. The small bowel is normal appearing. There is no evidence of appendiceal rupture or intra-abdominal fluid collection. There are no suspicious lytic or blastic lesions seen in the visualized osseous structures.
